3. cs.DB (Databases): The paper discusses the privacy of query profiles of database/search engine users and proposes a solution concept for preserving it. This is related to the field of databases. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the behavior of rational agents and proposes a solution concept for regulating their interactions. This is related to the field of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new solution concept for self-enforcing protocols that is efficient and fair. This is related to the field of machine learning, which deals with developing algorithms that can learn from data and make decisions.
